ScenarioText: You're about to give a public class presentation. As you sit through your classmates' presentations, you begin to think your presentation will be of inferior quality, and you start to feel nervous, suddenly, your name is called – it’s your turn to present.

You realise that your chosen field of study is no longer aligning with your evolving interests and values. You develop a profound sense of sadness. This emotional response is rooted in the grief of letting go of an identity you once held close and the uncertainty of what comes next.
